channel.title: Someone help me with this
channel.description:
Okay so, I recently started a Server. Now I have it online and all. I'm wanting people to join. I'm in the midst of making a .Jar file. But I can't seem to get it. Now, my server isn't the most organized. I have two folders. One for the client. And one for the source. I just don't know what files I need to put in the input for my .Jar . If anyone could help I would much appreciate it. And if you have team viewer I'll show you my problem.
Thanks guys.

item.title: Someone help me with this
item.dc:creator: @Dougyb Dougyb
item.description:
@Dougyb wrote:

There is really no where in my Folders I have a “Bin” . But I’ve tried the Folder with the CLASS Files in it. And Still same problem. Clicked it. Nothing will open. This may sound stupid , I’m not sure. But should the folder with all the CLASS files have the cache stuff in there?

EDIT : NVM . Thanks Pnut. It worked.

item.title: Someone help me with this
item.dc:creator: @mista_pnut mista pnut
item.description:
@mista_pnut wrote:

Put make input directory direct to wherever your class files are for your client. (You said they were all in one folder, so it’d be something like this “C:\Users\Username\Desktop\Folder Containing the Class files”)
